@suharshs thanks for your reply. Here is my repro example(Machine Translation Project origin from google group, origin_repro), i modified some of the code in order make it simpler for lite converter project.
Converting into frozen and lite model's code : code

I have a few questions.

  1. what are the different between python version toco(lite.py etc. tf.contrib.lite.TocoConverter.from_frozen_graph) and command version? which one is the newest ones?
  2. I have already used tf.graph_util.convert_variables_to_constants python script to convert normal saved model into frozen graph but it still appears NoOp.
  3. I tried tf.graph_util.remove_training_nodes function for removing training nodes(may contain NoOp?) but the model will be broken(unable to inference, it may change some of the Op of the old graph then it pops errors again.). strange thing is NoOp problem is passed during toco converting.

I'm using the most recent version of TF (7/27/2018)

@suharshs  thanks for your reply. Here is my [repro example](https://github.com/lkfo415579/nmt_custom)(**Machine Translation Project origin from google group**, [origin_repro](https://github.com/tensorflow/nmt)), i modified some of the code in order make it simpler for lite converter project. 
Converting into frozen and lite model's code : [code](https://github.com/lkfo415579/nmt_custom/blob/041dd8ffe4afcaf0dfe96d86d8de17a079372fcc/nmt/inference.py#L213)

I have a few questions.

1. what are the different between python version toco(**lite.py etc. tf.contrib.lite.TocoConverter.from_frozen_graph**) and command version? which one is the newest ones?
2. I have already used **tf.graph_util.convert_variables_to_constants** python script to convert normal saved model into frozen graph but it still appears NoOp.
3. I tried **tf.graph_util.remove_training_nodes function** for removing training nodes(may contain NoOp?) but the model will be broken(unable to inference, it may change some of the Op of the old graph then it pops errors again.). strange thing is **NoOp** problem is passed during toco converting.

I'm using the most recent version of TF (7/27/2018)

My structure of frozen graph
[structure.txt](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/files/2240393/structure.txt)
